Sunday Nwakanma, Umuahia The Governor of Abia State, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, on Wednesday approved a downward review of monthly emolument of all political appointees in the state subject to review upon attainment of general financial stability. In statement by the Secretary to Abia State Government, Chris Ezem, the state government said, “This decision is informed by the present economic crunch in the country occasioned by the global pandemic. “Going forward, all political appointees shall be entitled to their basic monthly salary excluding other allowances.” The statement directed all relevant government establishments to note the directive and implement accordingly. Copyright PUNCH.
